  "text": "These observations are relevant to pathogen mediated competition between livestock and wildlife, e.g. bovine TB in badgers. The badger (host 2) is undoubtedly a reservoir of infection in the UK and therefore has to be controlled for exclusion to happen. The situation with livestock is less clear, but it is not far from being a reservoir of infection if it is not already [CITATION_1] ).",
